Based upon the above discussion, a plausible mechanism for PEC degradation of TC over FeOOH-CQDs/BiVO4 was proposed (Fig. 7
                        ). With the efficient type-II heterojunction between FeOOH and BiVO4, as well as the excellent electronic conductivity of CQDs, the photogenerated holes would be easily transferred onto the surface of the photoelectrode, and subsequently reacted with the absorbed TC to achieve the degradation of TC. Meanwhile, the photogenerated electrons in CB of BiVO4 flowed towards Pt counter electrode, and subsequently being trapped by O2 to generate O2
                        −, which further reacted with TC to generate the degradation products.
